<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4545136>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 38. Dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views of the skull of Artibeus jamaicensis (AMNH 266321; male) from Paracou. Dorsal (C) and ventral (D) views of the skull of A. lituratus (AMNH 267492; male) from Paracou. Note that jamaicensis has a broad interorbital region, small postorbital processes, and three molars, whereas lituratus has a narrower interorbit, better developed postorbital processes, and lacks M3. Scale bars = 10 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4545136/files/figure.png" .
